      • decrypt

        public byte[] decrypt(java.math.BigInteger output)
        Transforms the encrypted ciphertext into the original string that was entered Theta Worst Case: theta(n^2), where n is the number of bytes Theta Best Case: theta(n^2) The runtime is influenced by the multiplication operation, as implemented in BigInteger Preconditions: You have an encrypted String, stored as a BigInteger Postconditions: The original plaintext is presented
        Parameters:
        output - - the encrypted string
        Returns:
        A decrypted byte array of the message
